     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="7"/>
   <head>In prayse of the Booke:</head>
   <lg>
      <l>SWeet is the paine which vertuous trauell brings,</l>
      <l>High is the place which wisedome doth commend,</l>
      <l>Sower is the ease of vices root that springs:</l>
      <l>Loue is the sea<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>e which idlenes doth lend.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>None getteth wealth that puts not from the shore,</l>
      <l>Paine breedeth honor, vertue winneth fame,</l>
      <l>Glorie doth follow, courage goes before,</l>
      <l>Though oft the vent, answeare not the same.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Vertuous attempts are voide of all shame,</l>
      <l>The base whome meanes obscurely doth keepe,</l>
      <l>Liues voyd of honor, dies without name,</l>
      <l>And in eternall darknes euer he doth sleepe.</l>
      <l>Therefore SINETES ti's then no blot,</l>
      <l>With mournefull Passions to lament thy lot.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>R. S. Esq.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
